data.description: This enchanting property, spanning 1.38 acres and featuring 4 bedrooms and 3.5 bathrooms, offers a haven of tranquility in the coveted West Mobile area of Semmes. Nestled in a serene community just off Wulff Road and a stone's throw from the pristine Big Creek Lake, this residence exudes warmth and charm.    Erected in 2003, the house boasts an abundance of space, ensuring a comfortable lifestyle for all. Key updates, including a new water well pump in 2019 and a modernized HVAC system in 2021, provide peace of mind for homeowners. The sizable laundry room, complete with a generous back door entrance, enhances the practicality of daily living.    During the cooler months, you can cozy up by the wood-burning fireplace, creating the perfect ambiance for fall and winter. As the seasons change, the property's proximity to water activities ensures endless entertainment and outdoor enjoyment during spring and summer.    Downstairs, a capacious open-concept great room and a warm, inviting kitchen and breakfast area beckon gatherings and memorable moments. Three spacious bedrooms provide comfort and privacy, while an expansive entertainment room with an accompanying bathroom on the upper level adds versatility to the living space.    Tucked amidst lush greenery, shielded from road noise, and occupying a private enclave of 1.38 acres, this 2400 square foot brick home embodies serenity and seclusion. Private, quiet, and inviting – this residence eagerly awaits your presence, promising a life of comfort and fulfillment. Your ideal home is calling!
